menu "Picsaver (SD JPEG)"

config PICSAVER_ENCRYPTION_PASSWORD
    string "Passphrase for AES-256-GCM file encryption"
    default ""
    help
        If non-empty, each JPEG is encrypted before writing; filenames use the .ucam suffix.
        Leave empty to save normal .jpg files.
        The same passphrase is used with tools/decrypt_ucam.py on your PC.
        Note: the passphrase is stored in firmware image and sdkconfig — not secret from someone with flash access.

endmenu
